ğŸ“Œ Traffic Flow in Architecture
Request (100.x.x.x Pod â†’ 10.x.x.x AWS Service)

1ï¸âƒ£ Pod (100.x.x.x) initiates a request.
2ï¸âƒ£ Traffic flows via the podâ€™s secondary ENI.
3ï¸âƒ£ Node routes traffic using VPC Route Table (local).
4ï¸âƒ£ Request reaches EC2, RDS, ALB, or any AWS service (10.x.x.x).

Response (10.x.x.x AWS Service â†’ 100.x.x.x Pod)

5ï¸âƒ£ AWS service sends response back to worker node.
6ï¸âƒ£ Node routes traffic back to the pod via the secondary ENI (100.x.x.x).
7ï¸âƒ£ Pod in 100.x.x.x receives the response.
